<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-20T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-20T09:00:00-05:00" n="856" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d856">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 341.622a/137</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-20T14:00:00+00:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 20, 1916, 2 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 3.42 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4335. Your 3318,<note n="1" xml:id="d856fn1">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_644">p.
                                644</ref>.</note> May 15, 12 noon, and my 4314,<note n="2" xml:id="d856fn2">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_645">p.
                                645</ref>.</note> May 16, 6 p. m. <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir
                                Edward Grey</persName> informed me to-day that all the persons taken
                            from the <hi rend="italic">China</hi> would be released in conformity
                            with his promise made to me on the 5th instant and on the terms
                            mentioned in his memorandum of the 8th instant transmitted in my cipher
                            telegram 4289,<note n="3" xml:id="d856fn3">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_642">p.
                                642</ref>.</note> May 12, 4 p. m. I am consequently addressing him a
                            note in the terms prescribed in your telegram 3320,<note n="1" xml:id="d856fn4">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_644">p.
                                644</ref>.</note> May 15, 4 p. m.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>